<BaseLayout title="EDRA57 Workshop" description="AI-Enabled Toolmaking for Architects â€” a hands-on workshop at EDRA57 exploring generative AI in architectural computation.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <header class="mb-12 animate-fade-up">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Teaching &middot; Workshop</p>
      <h1 class="mb-4">EDRA57 Workshop</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        AI-Enabled Toolmaking for Architects
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 0.1s;">
      <p>
        This workshop explores how architects can use generative AI not as a
        replacement for design thinking, but as a material for building
        custom computational tools. Rather than accepting off-the-shelf
        software, we prototype instruments tailored to specific design problems.
      </p>

      <h2>Workshop Format</h2>

      <p>
        Participants work through a series of hands-on exercises that
        demonstrate the workflow from problem identification to working
        prototype. The emphasis is on <strong>agency</strong>&mdash;giving
        architects the ability to shape their own computational environment.
      </p>

      <h2>Key Themes</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>Generative AI as construction material, not magic</li>
        <li>Rapid prototyping of discipline-specific tools</li>
        <li>The architect as toolmaker (historical and contemporary)</li>
        <li>Ethical considerations in AI-augmented practice</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Outcomes</h2>

      <p>
        Several tools on this site&mdash;including the
        <a href="/tools/hvac-calculator">HVAC Calculator</a> and
        <a href="/tools/echotrace">EchoTrace</a>&mdash;originated as
        demonstrations for this workshop, illustrating how targeted tools can
        emerge from practice-specific needs.
      </p>
    </div>

    <footer class="mt-16">
      <hr class="rule mb-6" />
      <a href="/teaching" class="text-sm text-text-secondary hover:text-accent transition-colors">
        &larr; Back to teaching
      </a>
    </footer>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
